
[1]disaffect

   DISAFFECT, v.t. [dis and affect.]

   1. To alienate affection; to make less friendly to; to make less
   faithful to a person, party or cause, or less zealous to support it; to
   make discontented or unfriendly ; as, an attempt was made to disaffect
   the army.

   2. To disdain, or dislike.

   3. To throw into disorder.
